# JA4proxy-testing — 18-B CVE allowlist
#
# Entries here are CVEs explicitly accepted for a bounded window. Each
# CVE below MUST be preceded by an `# expires: YYYY-MM-DD` comment.
# scripts/ci/check_image_scan.py fails if any entry is expired —
# forcing a decision to fix, re-justify with a new expiry, or remove.
#
# Severity response times (from PHASE_18 acceptance matrix):
#   CRITICAL → decision within 7 days, fix within 30
#   HIGH     → decision within 30 days, fix within 90
#
# Only CRITICAL is a hard merge gate today; HIGH is informational
# until chunk 18-B-2 tightens the gate. That's why the current
# entries are all CRITICAL.

# CVE-2023-24538 (CRITICAL) — Go html/template in redis:7-alpine.
# The redis:7-alpine image pins Go 1.18.2 via its upstream base and
# has not refreshed in ~2 years. Options: move to redis:7.4-alpine
# (newer base) or redis:8-alpine. The honeypot is not a Go html/
# template user — impact on our deployment is very low — but we
# still want to carry a newer base. Decision by expiry.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2023-24538

# CVE-2026-30836 (CRITICAL) — smallstep/certificates unauth'd code
# path, vendored into caddy:2-alpine. Caddy's cert handling is not
# on our public path (HAProxy terminates TLS as passthrough and
# Caddy only serves the static honeypot after JA4proxy), so exposure
# is bounded. Fix requires caddy image refresh against
# smallstep/certificates 0.30.0.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2026-30836

# CVE-2026-33186 (CRITICAL) — grpc-go authz bypass via HTTP/2 path
# validation. Appears in both caddy:2-alpine and
# prom/blackbox-exporter:latest. Neither exposes gRPC externally in
# our deployment; impact is internal. Awaiting upstream image refresh
# against grpc-go 1.79.3.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2026-33186
